ke "when imperturbably at work," in spite of its odd scheme of stressed and unstressed syllables ("---/---/"), nevertheless iambic (or, minus the first word, trochaic)? Try and answer.



Your V.3





TO: KIRILL NABOKOV

c. 1930

ALS, 2 pp.

Berlin

Dear Kirill,

